[2] French Guiana
Date: Fri 6 Feb 2009
Source: France Info [in French, trans. & summ. Mod.MPP, edited]
<http://209.85.229.132/search?q=cache:PJCe5qGkTeQJ:www.france-info.com/spip.php%3Farticle248850>


The Cayenne prefecture said that Guyana was entering into "an epidemic
phase of dengue" in a communique issued on Thursday evening [5 Feb 2009].
"The upsurge of cases of dengue and malaria in Guyana [French Guiana] since
the beginning of January [2009] has intensified over the last 2 weeks,"
according to the prefecture in its communique. "For dengue, the number of
laboratory confirmed cases is steadily increasing throughout the country."

In Cayenne and surrounding areas "this increase is described as "sensitive"
and "particularly important in Kourou and Saint Laurent du Maroni." 425
people were infected with dengue virus in January [2009] the health
authorities pointed out.

In mid-January [2009], one infant died of this disease in western Guyana
according to the newspaper France-French Guyana at the end of last month.
On Thursday [5 Feb 2009], the committee that monitors human diseases
transmitted by insects confirmed that "Guyana had passed into the phase of
a dengue epidemic," said the prefecture.

