[7] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro)
Date: Fri 6 Feb 2009
Source: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/rio/mat/2009/02/06/estado-do-rio-teve-567-casos-de-dengue-com-seis-mortes-sob-investigacao-754294687.asp>


Up to [4 Feb 2009], the state of Rio de Janeiro has recorded, in 2009, 567
dengue cases with 6 deaths (one in Sao Joao do Meriti, one in Queimados, 3
in Rio de Janeiro, and one in Duque de Caxias) under investigation. The
municipalities with the greatest number of cases are Rio de Janeiro (239
[cases]), Itaborai (62), Angra dos Reis (46), Nova Iguacu (43), and
Araruama (27). The age group with the greatest number of reported [dengue
cases] is 15-49 years of age.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed@promedmail.org>

[6 deaths among nearly 600 cases give a fatality rate of 10 per cent, which
is absurd for dengue. - Mod.JLS

It seems likely that dengue is significantly underreported here. - Mod.TY]

